column1: # Name: Life expectancy at 60 years, total

# Definition: The average number of remaining years of life expected by a hypothetical cohort of males or females alive at age 60 who would be subject during the remaining of their lives to the age- and sex-specific mortality rates of a given period. It is expressed as years.
# Data from the No Ceilings project: http://noceilings.org
# For more about the data, please visit http://noceilings.org/data
